    {
      "instruction": "<p>Mix the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>in a small bowl and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p><p>Tip: If your butter is not soft then microwave for a few secs or until soft to the touch but not melted!</p><p>Add your<strong> portobello mushroom[s] </strong>to a baking tray and top with the <strong>garlic butter</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the mushroom[s] is tender and juicy – this is your <strong>garlic roasted portobello mushroom</strong></p>",
